Female, adult
(
holotype
; 
Figs 14A–C
)

GENITALIA (
Fig. 18E
). Setae arranged linearly in two rows 2:6 on sternite 2 and 6 setae arranged linearly on sternite 3 below opening.

LEGS (
Fig. 17A–B
). All legs with tarsus longer than metatarsus; scarcely granulated; femur + patella of leg IV 2.11 times as long as broad; legs III and IV with articulation between femur and patella segments slightly oblique; tibiae and metatarsi of legs III and IV with tactile setae; tarsi of legs III and IV with tactile setae sub-basally; arolium shorter than claws, distally broadened and undivided, claws simple and not serrate.

Male, adult
(
allotype
; 
Fig. 15A–C
)

GENITALIA (
Fig. 18D
). Small rounded ejaculatory opening; setal arrangement: two rows of setae arranged 2:2 linearly above opening, 4 setae congregated directly under opening and 10 setae congregated below.
